      "content": "the platforms just say they cant find any suspicious logins. it's like the person—or the thing—using my accounts is already inside the system. it's actually scary because some of the posts are things I haven't even thought about in years, but the AI is saying them like it's part of my soul. if an AI can perfectly simulate my personality and my history to the point where nobody can tell the difference, doesn't that mean the \"real\" me is basically gone? like, if it's doing everything i would do, what's the difference between me and the ghost?",
